# SECTION 1 — ARCHITECTURE & CODEBASE REVIEW

## Critical Architecture Issues

**1. No Firestore Security Rules**
Every document in your database is publicly readable and writable by anyone on the internet. Someone can open Postman right now and delete every game in your database.

**2. No Error Boundaries**
Unhandled exceptions crash the entire app with no recovery path.

**3. Riverpod State Leaks**
`currentUserModelProvider` is a `FutureProvider` that doesn't invalidate on logout. After logout, stale user data persists in memory.

**4. No Offline Handling**
Zero offline support. No cached data, no offline indicators, no retry mechanisms.

**5. Seed Data Runs Every App Launch**
`seedSampleGames()` runs in `initState` of HomeScreen on every single launch. It checks if games exist but still makes a Firestore read call every time.

