# SECTION 3 — 30 EDGE CASES

1. User deletes account mid-game — other players see ghost participant
2. Two users create games at exact same millisecond — conflict check race condition
3. User changes phone → loses account (no account recovery)
4. Game date passes — should auto-archive, currently stays visible
5. All 22 players join simultaneously — race condition on capacity check
6. User is in game chat → host cancels game → chat still accessible but game doesn't exist
7. User stars a game → joins it → leaves it → stars still show game
8. User with no sports selected creates a game
9. User enters emoji in name field — initials getter may crash on emoji characters
10. Very long venue name overflows game card
11. Very long sport name (if someone adds custom sport somehow)
12. User opens same game detail on two devices simultaneously and joins on both
13. Host edits time while players are viewing game detail — they see stale time
14. Network drops exactly during OTP send — app shows loading forever
15. Network drops during game creation — game may or may not be created, user doesn't know
16. User force-closes app during profile setup — profile not saved
17. User tries to join game that was just made full by someone else (race condition)
18. Starred game list exceeds Firestore `whereIn` limit of 30 items
19. User changes device — `starredGameIds` lost (actually stored in Firestore, fine)
20. User has 0 joined games and 0 hosted games — Your Games shows empty correctly?
21. Firebase Auth token expires mid-session
22. Phone number with spaces or dashes entered
23. Copy-paste OTP from SMS — hidden characters may be included
24. User rotates screen mid-form — state preserved? (Web yes, mobile possibly no)
25. User with extremely slow connection sees loading spinners for 30+ seconds with no timeout
26. Two people with same name — no disambiguation in player list
27. Game with 1 player needed (minimum 1) — host joins, game immediately full
28. User taps back during OTP verification — goes to phone screen with wrong state
29. Date picker selects today but time is in the past
30. User opens app with airplane mode — no error shown, just infinite loading

